{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880872778,"sessionID":"ses_28540bef6ffeeDD4mpjspUk0Mf","part":{"id":"prt_d7abf9aad001VNCshc3TcfDPuj","messageID":"msg_d7abf8245001mTu1XBmR8NKkS0","sessionID":"ses_28540bef6ffeeDD4mpjspUk0Mf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5f81678fee7f4a59b93a8550c4b412c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router (data plane). This AR focuses on the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes, enabling users to bootstrap sessions and invoke agent payloads.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                          User Application                            │\n24: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n25:                                 │\n26:                                 │ AgentRuntimeClient\n27:                                 ▼\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                     agentcube/agent_runtime.py                       │\n30: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n31: │  │ AgentRuntimeClient                                             │  │\n32: │  │  - session_id (bootstrapped or provided)                       │  │\n33: │  │  - router_url resolution                                       │  │\n34: │  │  - Context manager lifecycle                                   │  │\n35: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37:                                 │\n38:                                 │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n39:                                 ▼\n40: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n41: │             agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py            │\n42: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n43: │  │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient                                    │  │\n44: │  │  - HTTP Session with connection pooling                        │  │\n45: │  │  - Session header: x-agentcube-session-id                      │  │\n46: │  │  - GET bootstrap_session_id()                                  │  │\n47: │  │  - POST invoke(payload)                                        │  │\n48: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n49: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n50:                                 │\n51:                                 │ HTTP Requests\n52:                                 ▼\n53: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n54: │                          Router (Data Plane)                         │\n55: │  - /v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/          │\n56: │  - JWT authentication (handled by Router)                           │\n57: │  - Session routing                                                  │\n58: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### Component Relationships\n62: \n63: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n64: |-----------|------|--------------|\n65: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level user-facing client | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, `utils/log.py` |\n66: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Low-level HTTP client for Router | `utils/http.py`, `requests` |\n67: | `create_session` | HTTP session factory | `requests`, `HTTPAdapter` |\n68: | `get_logger` | Logging utility | `logging` |\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Data Structures\n73: \n74: ### AgentRuntimeClient Instance Fields\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n78:     agent_name: str              # Target agent identifier\n79:     namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n80:     timeout: int                 # Read timeout seconds (default: 120)\n81:     connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout seconds (default: 5.0)\n82:     logger: logging.Logger       # Verbose logger instance\n83:     router_url: str              # Router base URL (from arg or ROUTER_URL env)\n84:     session_id: Optional[str]    # Bootstrapped or user-provided session ID\n85:     dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  # Data plane client instance\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Instance Fields\n89: \n90: ```python\n91: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n92:     SESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"  # Class constant\n93:     router_url: str              # Router base URL\n94:     namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace\n95:     agent_name: str              # Target agent identifier\n96:     timeout: int                 # Default read timeout (120)\n97:     connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (5.0)\n98:     base_url: str                # Full invocation URL path\n99:     session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### Base URL Construction\n103: \n104: ```python\n105: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n106: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### Invoke Payload Structure\n110: \n111: ```python\n112: payload: Dict[str, Any]  # Arbitrary JSON payload for agent invocation\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## API Contracts\n118: \n119: ### AgentRuntimeClient Public API\n120: \n121: | Method | Signature | Description |\n122: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n123: | `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace=\"default\", router_url=None, verbose=False, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` | Initialize client |\n124: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | Context manager entry |\n125: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | Context manager exit, calls `close()` |\n126: | `invoke` | `(payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout=None) -> Any` | Invoke agent with payload |\n127: | `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n128: \n129: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Public API\n130: \n131: | Method | Signature | Description |\n132: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n133: | `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` | Initialize data plane client |\n134: | `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | GET base URL to bootstrap session |\n135: | `invoke` | `(session_id, payload, timeout=None) -> Response` | POST payload to agent |\n136: | `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n137: \n138: ### HTTP Endpoints\n139: \n140: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n141: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n142: | `GET` | `{base_url}` | (session default) | None |\n143: | `POST` | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n144: \n145: ### Timeout Behavior\n146: \n147: | Scenario | Timeout Value |\n148: |----------|---------------|\n149: | `invoke(..., timeout=None)` | `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` → `(5.0, 120)` |\n150: | `invoke(..., timeout=30)` | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` → `(5.0, 30)` |\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Error Handling\n155: \n156: ### Exception Hierarchy\n157: \n158: ```python\n159: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n160:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n161:     pass\n162: \n163: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n164:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n165:     pass\n166: \n167: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n168:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n169:     pass\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Error Scenarios\n173: \n174: | Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n175: |----------|------------|---------|\n176: | Router URL missing | `ValueError` | \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\" |\n177: | Missing session header in bootstrap | `ValueError` | \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n178: | Invoke without session | `ValueError` | \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n179: | HTTP request failure | `requests.exceptions.*` | Propagated from requests library |\n180: \n181: ### Error Handling Flow\n182: \n183: ```\n184: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n185: │                     invoke(payload, timeout)                         │\n186: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n187:                                 │\n188:                                 ▼\n189: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n190: │              Check session_id is not None                            │\n191: │  if not session_id: raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id...\")  │\n192: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n193:                                 │\n194:                                 ▼\n195: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n196: │              POST to base_url with headers                           │\n197: │  Headers: x-agentcube-session-id, Content-Type: application/json    │\n198: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n199:                                 │\n200:                                 ▼\n201: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n202: │              Return response.json()                                  │\n203: │  (or raw Response object from data plane client)                    │\n204: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ## Testing Strategy\n210: \n211: ### Test Categories\n212: \n213: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n214: |----------|-------|-------|\n215: | Unit Tests | Client logic, URL construction, header management | pytest, unittest.mock |\n216: | Integration Tests | HTTP interactions with mock server | pytest, responses library |\n217: | E2E Tests | Full workflow against Router | pytest, real Router instance |\n218: \n219: ### Test Scenarios\n220: \n221: #### Unit Tests\n222: \n223: | Test Case | Description |\n224: |-----------|-------------|\n225: | `test_router_url_resolution` | Verify Router URL from arg vs env var |\n226: | `test_base_url_construction` | Verify URL path `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` |\n227: | `test_session_header_constant` | Verify `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n228: | `test_context_manager_enter_exit` | Verify `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `close()` |\n229: \n230: #### Integration Tests\n231: \n232: | Test Case | Description |\n233: |-----------|-------------|\n234: | `test_bootstrap_session_id_success` | Mock GET returning `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n235: | `test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header` | Mock GET without header → raises ValueError |\n236: | `test_invoke_with_session` | Mock POST with payload and verify headers |\n237: | `test_invoke_without_session` | Call invoke before bootstrap → raises ValueError |\n238: | `test_invoke_timeout_override` | Verify timeout tuple `(5.0, 30)` when passed |\n239: \n240: #### E2E Tests\n241: \n242: | Test Case | Description |\n243: |-----------|-------------|\n244: | `test_e2e_agent_invoke` | Full workflow: bootstrap session → invoke → validate response |\n245: \n246: ### Test File Locations\n247: \n248: | File | Purpose |\n249: |------|---------|\n250: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | Unit + integration tests for AgentRuntimeClient |\n251: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Unit + integration tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n252: | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | E2E test script (reference from spec) |\n253: \n254: ### Mocking Strategy\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: # Example: Mock bootstrap GET\n258: import responses\n259: import pytest\n260: \n261: @responses.activate\n262: def test_bootstrap_session_id():\n263:     responses.get(\n264:         \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\",\n265:         headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-123\"}\n266:     )\n267:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(...)\n268:     session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n269:     assert session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## File Structure\n275: \n276: | Path | Role |\n277: |------|------|\n278: | `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation (NEW) |\n279: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation (NEW) |\n280: | `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n281: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n282: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | Tests for AgentRuntimeClient (NEW) |\n283: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Tests for data plane client (NEW) |\n284: | `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` | Usage example (NEW) |\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Dependencies\n289: \n290: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n291: |---------|---------|---------|\n292: | `requests` | (latest) | HTTP client for Router communication |\n293: | `PyJWT` | >=2.0.0 | JWT handling (used by other clients, included for consistency) |\n294: | `cryptography` | (latest) | Cryptographic support for JWT |\n295: | `pytest` | (dev) | Test framework |\n296: | `responses` | (dev) | HTTP mocking library |\n297: | `unittest.mock` | (stdlib) | Mocking utilities |\n298: \n299: ### pyproject.toml Dependencies\n300: \n301: ```toml\n302: dependencies = [\n303:     \"requests\",\n304:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n305:     \"cryptography\",\n306: ]\n307: \n308: [project.optional-dependencies]\n309: dev = [\n310:     \"pytest\",\n311:     \"pytest-cov\",\n312:     \"responses\",\n313: ]\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Implementation Notes\n319: \n320: ### Router URL Resolution\n321: \n322: ```python\n323: router_url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n324: if not router_url:\n325:     raise ValueError(\"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\")\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ### Session Bootstrap Flow\n329: \n330: ```python\n331: def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n332:     resp = self.session.get(self.base_url, timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout))\n333:     session_id = resp.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n334:     if not session_id:\n335:         raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n336:     return session_id\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ### Invoke Implementation\n340: \n341: ```python\n342: def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Response:\n343:     effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n344:     headers = {self.SESSION_HEADER: session_id, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n345:     resp = self.session.post(\n346:         self.base_url,\n347:         json=payload,\n348:         headers=headers,\n349:         timeout=(self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n350:     )\n351:     return resp\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ### Context Manager Pattern\n355: \n356: ```python\n357: def __enter__(self):\n358:     return self\n359: \n360: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n361:     self.close()\n362:     return False  # Don't suppress exceptions\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### Connection Pooling\n366: \n367: ```python\n368: from requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n369: \n370: def create_session(pool_connections: int = 10, pool_maxsize: int = 10) -> Session:\n371:     session = requests.Session()\n372:     adapter = HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n373:     session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n374:     session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n375:     return session\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### No Authorization on Data Plane\n379: \n380: The Router handles JWT authentication. The SDK does NOT set `Authorization` header on data plane requests—only the session header.\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## References\n385: \n386: - Spec: `changes/AR-028/spec.md`\n387: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n388: - Tasks: `changes/AR-028/tasks.md`\n389: - Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n390: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n391: - Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`\n\n(End of file - total 391 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router (data plane). This AR focuses on the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes, enabling users to bootstrap sessions and invoke agent payloads.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775880872758,"end":1775880872776}}}}
